WEBVTT

00:02.419 --> 00:04.304
Oh, I'll see you guys later.

00:05.839 --> 00:08.057
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:08.591 --> 00:10.778
You realize this school
has a Litter Society?

00:10.802 --> 00:12.562
Mm, for or against?

00:12.929 --> 00:14.063
Gum?

00:14.264 --> 00:15.282
Mm.

00:15.306 --> 00:17.525
- This is your last piece.
- It's okay.

00:23.273 --> 00:26.034
It says that they
meet on Mondays.

00:26.359 --> 00:29.714
Heal the Bay, is
Tuesdays and Thursdays.

00:29.738 --> 00:31.831
I might be able to swing
them both, unless...

00:32.031 --> 00:33.458
You think those are too similar?

00:33.783 --> 00:35.386
You're actually joining these?

00:35.410 --> 00:37.712
I mean, don't take this
the wrong way, but you?

00:37.829 --> 00:39.390
I gotta get more stuff
on my transcript,

00:39.414 --> 00:41.799
you know, activities, awards.

00:43.042 --> 00:44.437
Maybe I could save a life.

00:44.461 --> 00:45.595
You know? Um...

00:46.254 --> 00:48.139
I don't know, uh... uh...

00:48.423 --> 00:50.901
Uh, Heimlich someone in the
cafeteria or something.

00:50.925 --> 00:52.653
That would impress
colleges, don't you think?

00:52.677 --> 00:55.823
Yeah, well, if you're gonna ask me to
choke on a chicken bone during lunch,

00:55.847 --> 00:57.241
that's where I draw the line.

00:57.265 --> 00:58.691
Some friend you are.

00:58.850 --> 01:01.037
Class elections are coming
up, and you could run.

01:01.061 --> 01:02.862
Ah, that's a little geeky.

01:03.188 --> 01:04.331
Well, not on a transcript.

01:04.355 --> 01:06.250
And you'd win. I mean,
you'd definitely win.

01:06.274 --> 01:07.909
Who wouldn't vote for you?

01:08.526 --> 01:09.879
So, what, you mean,

01:09.903 --> 01:11.297
like president?

01:11.321 --> 01:13.632
Mm, Brian Cohen wins
that every year.

01:13.656 --> 01:15.009
How about vice president?

01:15.033 --> 01:16.459
Vice president?

01:16.576 --> 01:18.095
I can do that.

01:18.119 --> 01:19.754
And, and when you
think about it,

01:19.871 --> 01:22.840
what are the odds of the senior
class president dying in office?

01:24.167 --> 01:26.552
- Although with my luck...
- God, Bailey.

01:29.506 --> 01:31.516
You sure about this
chicken bone thing?

01:31.633 --> 01:33.277
- Definitely.
- Okay.

01:33.301 --> 01:35.269
- I'll see you.
- Bye.

01:38.473 --> 01:40.858
All right, you guys,
meet me at my locker.

01:43.228 --> 01:44.737
Griffin.

01:45.647 --> 01:47.281
Hey, how's it goin'?

01:47.607 --> 01:50.118
All right. You?

01:52.529 --> 01:53.955
Um,

01:54.322 --> 01:57.583
Listen, about what
happened with us,

01:57.742 --> 01:59.136
it was nice and everything.

01:59.160 --> 02:02.389
I mean, I didn't not like
it, but there's Justin,

02:02.413 --> 02:04.715
and I love Justin.

02:05.208 --> 02:06.227
A lot.

02:06.251 --> 02:09.604
Um, and you and I could be
friends, like we've been.

02:09.628 --> 02:11.440
I mean, I still want us to,

02:11.464 --> 02:13.025
just nothing else.

02:13.049 --> 02:14.892
I mean, we can't
be anything more.

02:16.678 --> 02:18.020
Okay?

02:18.513 --> 02:20.064
I hear you.

02:20.223 --> 02:21.566
Good.

02:22.058 --> 02:23.609
Good. Okay.

02:23.685 --> 02:25.955
Um, so I should go to French.

02:25.979 --> 02:27.289
Yeah, right.

02:27.313 --> 02:28.948
So I'll see you sometime.

02:29.816 --> 02:31.534
- Hey.
- Yeah?

